    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 3rd with a balanced offensive outlook, led by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (82.13), who headlines our starts today. His massive 18% boost from the SP skill matchup against Meiner Kelly and an 87% stolen base probability\u2014aided by a favorable wind\u2014make him our most valuable asset in the hunt for scarcity points. **Junior Caminero** (75.14) also presents a high-floor profile, leveraging a significant SP skill advantage against Mahle to overcome a park penalty. While **Trea Turner** (67.99) and **Colt Keith** (66.91) don't reach the \"Elite\" threshold, their high-leverage lineup positions and favorable matchups against Paddack and Leiter make them essential cogs in our pursuit of Roto category dominance.\n\nWe are forced to navigate a few difficult platoon situations, most notably with **Yordan Alvarez** (63.71), who maintains a strong score despite a 9% penalty for the L/L matchup against Suarez, simply due to his elite 0.430 xwOBA. Conversely, we are keeping **Jerar Encarnacion** (41.97) on the bench; he was the closest consideration for the lineup, but ultimately his 6% penalty for the eighth spot in the order and a tough matchup against Matz tipped the scales in favor of our higher-floor starters. We are monitoring **Hyeseong Kim** (56.00) closely, as his stolen base equity is currently capped by a 4% drag from a pitcher adept at holding runners, representing the primary risk factor in today\u2019s projection. Finally, remain mindful that **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** remain sidelined, leaving us without additional depth should late-inning defensive switches impact our active roster.",
